title: Excruciation Exam
description: The first marathon in the Texas Marathon series for 2007 will be the Talon Trails Excruciation Exam.  The race will be approximately 85 miles of singletrack and farm roads, incorporating trails at both Rocky Hill Ranch and Bluff Creek Ranch. Cost of the event is $55, $65 day of.
registration: Ragistration will be available online or at the event. Pre registration is preferred. Mail checks to Talon Trails, 512 Eberhart Ln, #1303 Austin, TX 78745.
directions: The race will start at Bluff creek ranch, at sunrise. www.bcrwarda.com

title: Texas Cup Series hosted by the Superdrome
University of Texas Cycling Race Weekend
Medical Colleagues of Texas Road Race
The Southerns
description:
South Central Collegiate Cycling Conference Championships hosted by Stephen F Austin.

Road Race - 4/28, Starting at 8am
Team Time Trial - 4/28, Starting at 4pm
Criterium - 4/29 - starting at 9am
course:
Road Race - 24 Mile lap with 1/2 mile dirt section after 2 mile climb. Perfect for breakaways, strong uphill finishing skills required. 

Criterium - 0.8 mile on a flat fast course with both right and left hand turns.

Team Time Trial - 11 mile out-out-back set up.
registration:
Pre-registration is preferred by mailing in entry form along with standard athlete release to address posted on SCCCC Web Server. Registration Friday night on SFA campus in HPE building. 

Late registration available on race day, but must be registered 30 minutes prior to start time.
notes:
Open to collegiate riders from the SCCCC only. Must have previous race qualifications to race in catagories at event.
Team time trial - 3/4 Men, 3/4 Women wheel of 3rd rider used to determine time. (team points only).
directions:
Road Race - From Campus, head North on North St, left on Stallings Dr under overpass and take right at T intersection. Head straight until you see parking on left.

Criterium - From Campus, head south on North Street until it becomes US 59, continue south to Lufkin, TX and take a right on Lufkin Ave. Parking behind closed downtown area.

Team Time Trial - Head south from Campus on North st til it becomes US 59. Take a right on 2782 and head to parking at National Park.

title: Huntsville Classic XI presented by Bike Lane Houst
Pain on the Plains/TMBRA Fall Series Race #3
Katy Trail AAC Criterium
description: 7am Time Trial from the BOTTOM of the Katy Trail to the TOP of the Katy Trail at Knox Street. Distance is roughly 2 miles. 9am Start for Criterium around American Airlines Center and the \"W\" Hotel.
course: TT course will begin at the bottom of the Katy Trail, opposite American Airlines Center. Riders will race UP the trail to \"David\'s Way\", and will return to the AAC via Turtle Creek Blvd. The Crit course will start and finish at the NE entrance to the American Airlines Center, and will travel CLOCKWISE down Houston Street to High Market Street, where riders will turn RIGHT. Riders will turn RIGHT again on Victory Avenue, and will travel the length of Victory to the hairpin, where they will turn RIGHT, back on to Houston Street. The Start/Finish will be roughly 300 meters from the final turn. Total distance is about 1.1 miles.
registration: Registration will be via BikeReg.com. Day-of-race registration is available.
notes: Race will be held in conjunction with Katy Trail Days, a local Dallas Park. TT results will be scored separately from the Criterium. Primes will be available in all races. A \'citizens\' race will also be available. Warmup and cooldown locations are available in the parking lot areas.
directions: American Airlines Center is located just off Stemmons Freeway in Dallas. Parking will occur at the NORTHERNMOST parking lot, on ALAMO street. To get to Alamo from Stemmons, take the Oak Lawn Avenue Exit and go EAST approximately .1 mile. On Harry Hines, go SOUTH approximately .25 miles to the first light. Turn RIGHT on to Alamo and follow directions. Parking is another .3 miles up.

title: Sun & Ski Presents the Rocky Hill Round Up Cyclocr
Sun and Ski Sports Presents the Rocky Hill Roundup
description:
Sun and Ski Sports Presents the Rocky Hill Roundup
Season Finale of the Sugar Cycles Fall Cup
November 11, 2007
course:
7-10 mile course consisteing of mostly singletrack.
12 and unders will run a shorter course. 1 Full lap for Beginners, 2 laps for Sport and older Experts, 3 laps for younger experts.
registration: Online registration available at BikeReg.com, or mail in via form on TMBRA.org. $30 for adults, $15 for Juniors 15-18, $10 for Juniors 12 and under. $5 Non license holder fee. Onsite registration is $5 extra for adults.
notes: Sport classes start at 0900, Expert classes start at 1100, Beginner classes start at 130. The ranch charges a $5 per day per person land use fee, do not include with registration.
directions: Rocky Hill Ranch is on FM 153, 2 miles north of Hwy 71.
